fileManagerAPI

Class FileWriter<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fileManagerAPI.CommonFileOperations<E,java.io.BufferedWriter>
      • fileManagerAPI.FileWriter<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - generic type of data returned by the method manipulateFile().
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileManager<E,java.io.BufferedWriter>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Writer

    public abstract class FileWriter<E>
extends CommonFileOperations<E,java.io.BufferedWriter>
    This class implements the operations used to be able to write lines into a file. Moreover, it propagates the implementation of the method manipulateFile() through the modifier abstract. To Note that the generic type of data T, defined in FileManager and propagate in CommonFileOperations has been fixed in this class to be an BufferedWriter object. A call to the function openFile() will generate the proper initialization of the data returned by getFileMatipolator() with respect to the parameters given in inputs to the constructor. Since file manipulator is of rime BufferedWriter it is possible to just use:
      String line = "something to write"
      getFileMatipolator().write( line);

     To make permanent the changes over the file closeFile() should be called. This will also effect the value of the writer: getFileMatipolator(). It must be reinitialized to be used again.
    Author:
    Buoncomapagni Luca
    See Also:
    CommonFileOperations, FileManager

    • Constructor Detail

      • FileWriter

        public FileWriter(java.lang.String path,
          java.lang.Boolean isRelative,
          java.lang.Boolean appendFile)
        Constructor which just call the construction of CommonFileOperations and uses the third parameter to set the method setAppendingFileType(Boolean).
        Parameters:
        path - is the directory path to the file in relative or absolute notation.
        isRelative - if it is true, it identifies that the parameter path defines a relative path. Otherwise, if it is false, it denotes that the parameter path is an absolute address.
        appendFile - if it is true that the new lines will be written at the end of the file. Otherwise, if it is false, the file will be replaced with an empty one, and than the data will be written on it.
